Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

Job Description:
Remote Psychiatrist Position - Full Time and Part Time Opportunities, 100% Telepsychiatry. Live Anywhere!
Talkiatry is currently seeking 100% Remote Telehealth Psychiatrists to join our national team of licensed providers as we expand into new markets across the US! With plans to open office space in a number of cities in 2022, providers will have the option to work 100% telehealth OR on-site. We are happy to assist with covering licensure expenses (State medical license, DEA, CDS, etc) as well as managing the process for submitting licensing applications!
Founded in April 2020, Talkiatry has been built from the ground up by psychiatrists. We have rapidly grown to a team of over 50 clinicians comprised mostly of BC/BE Psychiatrists hailing from the top training programs across the region.
We provide in-network, outpatient treatment for children and adults with depression, anxiety, attention deficit, and other disorders. Talkiatry does not provide intensive outpatient or partial hospitalization programs. We believe that solving the accessibility issues in mental health care begins with taking care of our doctors. We provide solutions to the challenges that psychiatrists are facing - from a lack of front and back-office infrastructure and support in private practice settings to being overworked and underpaid by hospitals, clinics, and other institutions. Talkiatry aims to bridge the current gap in outpatient psychiatry by providing high quality, respected medical care in a modern setting with modern tools.

Referring a patient for psychological testing to determine a diagnosis and its severity

Exploring the patients’ past experiences to learn how they affect their current state of mind and behavior (psychoanalysis)
Helping patients change their thought processes and behavior (Cognitive Behavioral Therapy or CBT)
Prescribing medication that can alter chemical imbalances affecting the patient’s state of mind and behavior

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

*
Minded’s guiding principle is to provide high quality services that are streamlined and responsive to patient and customer needs, as well as clinical outcomes for patients that meet objective, industry standard measures.

With Minded you have one less thing to worry about.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

*
Minded’s guiding principle is to provide high quality services that are streamlined and responsive to patient and customer needs, as well as clinical outcomes for patients that meet objective, industry standard measures.
About Minded
Renewing medication for anxiety, insomnia and depression should be easy. So we eliminated the need to travel, wait, and tell your story yet again. We’ll renew your prescriptions quickly, make sure you never run out, and give you ongoing care and support. And we made it affordable to everyone, even without insurance. With Minded you have one less thing to worry about.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

Minded is seeking a part-time psychiatrist on our growing team. The position will provide remote supervision of Psychiatric Mental Health Nurse Practitioners and serve as their collaborating physician where required. This position will help Minded ensure clinical quality and outcomes as aligned with Minded’s clinical vision and philosophy of care.
*
Minded’s guiding principle is to provide high quality services that are streamlined and responsive to patient and customer needs, as well as clinical outcomes for patients that meet objective, industry standard measures.
About Minded
Renewing medication for anxiety, insomnia and depression should be easy. So we eliminated the need to travel, wait, and tell your story yet again. We’ll renew your prescriptions quickly, make sure you never run out, and give you ongoing care and support. And we made it affordable to everyone, even without insurance. With Minded you have one less thing to worry about.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

Job Title: Remote Psychiatrist - Flexible Scheduling, 100% Telehealth w/Benefits!
Job Description:
Remote Psychiatrist Position - Full Time and Part Time Opportunities, 100% Telepsychiatry. Live Anywhere!
Talkiatry is currently seeking 100% Remote Telehealth Psychiatrists to join our national team of licensed providers as we expand into new markets across the US! With plans to open office space in a number of cities in 2022, providers will have the option to work 100% telehealth OR on-site. We are happy to assist with covering licensure expenses (State medical license, DEA, CDS, etc) as well as managing the process for submitting licensing applications!
Founded in April 2020, Talkiatry has been built from the ground up by psychiatrists. We have rapidly grown to a team of over 50 clinicians comprised mostly of BC/BE Psychiatrists hailing from the top training programs across the region.
We provide in-network, outpatient treatment for children and adults with depression, anxiety, attention deficit, and other disorders. Talkiatry does not provide intensive outpatient or partial hospitalization programs. We believe that solving the accessibility issues in mental health care begins with taking care of our doctors. We provide solutions to the challenges that psychiatrists are facing - from a lack of front and back-office infrastructure and support in private practice settings to being overworked and underpaid by hospitals, clinics, and other institutions. Talkiatry aims to bridge the current gap in outpatient psychiatry by providing high quality, respected medical care in a modern setting with modern tools.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

We are happy to assist with covering licensure expenses (State medical license, DEA, CDS, etc) as well as managing the process for submitting licensing applications!
Founded in April 2020, Talkiatry has been built from the ground up by psychiatrists. We have rapidly grown to a team of over 50 clinicians comprised mostly of BC/BE Psychiatrists hailing from the top training programs across the region.
We provide in-network, outpatient treatment for children and adults with depression, anxiety, attention deficit, and other disorders. Talkiatry does not provide intensive outpatient or partial hospitalization programs. We believe that solving the accessibility issues in mental health care begins with taking care of our doctors. We provide solutions to the challenges that psychiatrists are facing - from a lack of front and back-office infrastructure and support in private practice settings to being overworked and underpaid by hospitals, clinics, and other institutions. Talkiatry aims to bridge the current gap in outpatient psychiatry by providing high quality, respected medical care in a modern setting with modern tools.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

JOIN THE LARGEST MENTAL HEALTH PRIVATE PRACTICE IN FL!
ABOUT US: We are a growing practice, serving Fort Lauderdale, FL for over 7 years. Our CEO, Dr. Peter Ventre is Chief of Psychiatry at Broward Health Medical Center and he is very passionate about patient care, research, medical education!
We are one of the few psychiatry practices with a fully certified Electronics Medical Records (EMR) system, fully digital (that means no paper charts). Our full-time staff handles all administrative and support functions so you can focus solely on patient care and good charting. Our office has home-like comfortable, furnished rooms, computers, and high-speed internet access. If you are interested in research, we also have our sister facility Research Centers of America (RCA) where Dr. Ventre is the director and principal investigator. RCA runs clinical trials for psychiatric pharmaceuticals.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

JOIN THE LARGEST MENTAL HEALTH PRIVATE PRACTICE IN FL!
ABOUT US: We are a growing practice, serving Fort Lauderdale, FL for over 7 years. Our CEO, Dr. Peter Ventre is Chief of Psychiatry at Broward Health Medical Center and he is very passionate about patient care, research, medical education!
We are one of the few psychiatry practices with a fully certified Electronics Medical Records (EMR) system, fully digital (that means no paper charts). Our full-time staff handles all administrative and support functions so you can focus solely on patient care and good charting. Our office has home-like comfortable, furnished rooms, computers, and high-speed internet access. If you are interested in research, we also have our sister facility Research Centers of America (RCA) where Dr. Ventre is the director and principal investigator. RCA runs clinical trials for psychiatric pharmaceuticals.

Job Title: Remote Psychiatrist - Flexible Scheduling, 100% Telehealth w/Benefits!
Job Description:
Remote Psychiatrist Position - Full Time and Part Time Opportunities, 100% Telepsychiatry. Live Anywhere!
Talkiatry is currently seeking 100% Remote Telehealth Psychiatrists to join our national team of licensed providers as we expand into new markets across the US! With plans to open office space in a number of cities in 2022, providers will have the option to work 100% telehealth OR on-site. We are happy to assist with covering licensure expenses (State medical license, DEA, CDS, etc) as well as managing the process for submitting licensing applications!
Founded in April 2020, Talkiatry has been built from the ground up by psychiatrists. We have rapidly grown to a team of over 50 clinicians comprised mostly of BC/BE Psychiatrists hailing from the top training programs across the region.
We provide in-network, outpatient treatment for children and adults with depression, anxiety, attention deficit, and other disorders. Talkiatry does not provide intensive outpatient or partial hospitalization programs. We believe that solving the accessibility issues in mental health care begins with taking care of our doctors. We provide solutions to the challenges that psychiatrists are facing - from a lack of front and back-office infrastructure and support in private practice settings to being overworked and underpaid by hospitals, clinics, and other institutions. Talkiatry aims to bridge the current gap in outpatient psychiatry by providing high quality, respected medical care in a modern setting with modern tools.

Job Description

Compensation is subject to availability and dedication to patient care. Dedicated, full time physicians have unlimited earning potential.
Services Provided
Psychiatric Services: Psychiatric evaluation and on-going psychotropic medication management.
Psychotherapy Services: Individual therapy, family therapy, and group therapy.
Behavioral Rounds: Fully integrated interdisciplinary care plan meetings with specific focus on the reduction of psychotropic medications and behavioral problems, as well as the resident's progress toward treatment goals.

The Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai affiliated with Elmhurst Hospital Center, serving the culturally diverse community of Western Queens, is seeking a full time board certified/board eligible Adult Psychiatrist to join its Adult Outpatient Division and a board certified/board eligible Psychiatrist to join its overnight (flexible hours-8, 10, 12 or 16 hour shifts) CPEP Division.
Elmhurst Hospital Center’s Psychiatry Department serves a multi-cultural population of adults, children and families. We offer a full spectrum of services including: Adult/Child Inpatient services with a Psychiatric ICU, Co-Occurring Disorders Unit and Women’s Forensic Unit; a high volume CPEP; culturally competent Asian and Spanish Units; Mobile Crisis Team; Adult and Adolescent Partial Hospitalization Programs; Ambulatory Adult and Child programs; Chemical Dependency; and Home Based Services. In addition, we also offer faculty appointment with the Icahn School of Medicine at Mount Sinai Health System. The Department collaborates with numerous schools in providing training programs in the areas of psychology, nursing and medicine. This is an excellent opportunity to join a multidisciplinary team working with a diverse patient population.

EXPERIENCE: Emergency Psychiatry, Consult Liaison Psychiatry or Inpatient Psychiatry are ideal. Ability to work in a collaborative, growth-oriented, environment is essential.

Job Title: Tele Psychiatrist (MD or DO only, NY license or able to obtain required)
Job Description:
Hiring at Skypiatrist.com, a telepsychiatry private practice. Due to the ongoing pandemic, demand for telepsychiatry has risen, and the benefits are becoming increasingly obvious. We have been an exclusively telepsychiatry practice since 2016, have worked out all the kinks and are ready to help you build your own telepsychiatry practice.
Our goal is to create the best psychiatric practice for patients and doctors. For doctors, you have the convenience of working from home and choosing your own hours. Your schedule is set the day before you see patients - no waiting around for last minute add-ons. Unlike other telemedicine outpatient positions, you will not be taking over an unknown physician's practice, with patients who are unstable or prescribed large amounts of controlled substances from a pill-mill. You will be building your practice from new patients, and you are given autonomy as far as whom you choose to accept. You will not be forced to use a Byzantine EMR designed by administrators that don’t take into account clinicians’ needs for simple, clear, customizable notes (at Skypiatrist, you can design your own note or choose from simple templates). We will handle billing, marketing, website maintenance, and administrative needs so you can focus on seeing patients. The founder and Chief Medical Officer is a psychiatrist, and is sensitive to the needs of doctors for good patient care.

JOIN THE LARGEST MENTAL HEALTH PRIVATE PRACTICE IN FL!
ABOUT US: We are a growing practice, serving Fort Lauderdale, FL for over 7 years. Our CEO, Dr. Peter Ventre is Chief of Psychiatry at Broward Health Medical Center and he is very passionate about patient care, research, medical education!
We are one of the few psychiatry practices with a fully certified Electronics Medical Records (EMR) system, fully digital (that means no paper charts). Our full-time staff handles all administrative and support functions so you can focus solely on patient care and good charting. Our office has home-like comfortable, furnished rooms, computers, and high-speed internet access. If you are interested in research, we also have our sister facility Research Centers of America (RCA) where Dr. Ventre is the director and principal investigator. RCA runs clinical trials for psychiatric pharmaceuticals.
